  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Grotta Giusti hotel is housed in a 19th Century Villa that has been fully restored to its original magnificence. Set in the beautiful <a data-udi="umb://document/ddef5c7c9bdb475792ae27614a6308b8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ddef5c7c9bdb475792ae27614a6308b8}" title="Northern Tuscany &amp; Montecatini">Tuscan</a> countryside just three and a half miles from Montecatini Terme and half way between the Tuscan cities of Lucca and Florence. Unique to the hotel is the thermal caves which are the largest in Europe, you can enjoy natural springs of varying temperatures. This is a place to truly relax and unwind, made easy to do so by the beautiful natural surrounding and the natural Thermal spa, where you can experience a steam bath in the natural caves, pools with hydro massage and soothing waterfalls. If that’s not enough to keep you relaxed and entertained, the hotel offers a wide range of sporting facilities, including tennis courts and a golf course (all payable locally).</p>
<p>Enjoy a pre-dinner drink or cocktail in the Bar Il Poeta amidst the splendour of the Gusti Room with its magnificent frescoed ceiling. This was the room in which local dignitaries would be hosted and entertained back in the 19th Century. After, dine at the new Restaurant La Veranda where on warm evenings you can also choose to eat outside on the pergola or under the stars on the terrace beside the pool. The guest rooms retain the historic luxury and refinement of the historic villa, adorned with luxury fabrics, paintings and antiques. In the morning wake up and find yourself in a comfortable and calm oasis.</p>
<p>Car hire is recommended for this hotel. Grotta Giusti is approx. 50 mins from Pisa Airport</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
