  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong><u>Restaurants &amp; Bars</u></strong></p>
<p><strong>La Veranda Restaurant </strong>offers a variety of Tuscan dishes, created by chef Guido Lotti, ispired by the land, tradition and innovation of Tuscany. Enjoy a culinary delight in an elegant and intimate setting. Dine in the lavish hall, outside on the pergola or by the pool.</p>
<p><strong><u>Natural Spa</u></strong></p>
<p>The hotel is built above some of the largest thermal caves in Europe. The ancient cave system and the thermal waters of the Grotta Giusti hot springs supply the Grotta Gusti Spa with its steam bath in the natural grotto, massages, spa programmes and treatments. Access to the Grotta Gusti Spa and Treatment services are payable locally. Guests have access to the Bioaguam thermal pools with hydro massages and a waterfall free of charge.</p>
<p>The Grotta Giusti thermal spa is open Mon – Sat 9:00am - 7:00pm &amp; Sun 10:00am to 7:00pm.</p>
<p>The Therapeutic Thermal Pool is open every day from 10:00am - 6:00pm.</p>
<p><strong><u>Pool</u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Outdoor Swimming Pool</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><u>Activities </u></strong></p>
<p><strong>Fitness centre </strong>with the latest cardio equipment</p>
<p>Payable locally:</p>
<ul>
<li>Fitness classes &amp; personal training sessions</li>
<li>Golf course</li>
<li>Tennis court</li>
<li>Horse riding</li>
<li>Bike hire</li>
<li>Cave diving</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><u>General Facilities </u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Wifi</li>
<li>Private Parking</li>
</ul>]]></facilityDescription>
